This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as subspace clustering is a common problem in computer vision applications such as image segmentation and object recognition. The use of low rank representation and weighted nuclear norm minimization also suggests a focus on machine learning and optimization, which are covered in the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also involves matrix manipulation and optimization, which are relevant to the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the use of convex programming and optimization techniques suggests a possible connection to information theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
